---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="Physiotherapy in Clapham"
	description="Evidence-led physiotherapy in Clapham, London. From injury recovery to long-term condition management, we help you move better, feel stronger and return to what you love."
>
	<PageHero
		title="in Clapham"
		highlight="Physiotherapy"
		subtitle="Evidence-led physiotherapy that helps you understand how your body moves, why things have gone wrong, and what needs to change."
		breadcrumb="Physiotherapy"
	/>

	<section class="rich-content">
		<div class="container">
			<p>Pain, injury, or loss of function can change how you move, and how you live. At Balance, physiotherapy is about more than symptom relief. It's about understanding how your body moves, why things have gone wrong, and what needs to change to get you back to full capacity.</p>
			<p>We take a clinical, evidence-led approach to every case. From your first session, we assess how you move, not just where it hurts, then build a plan around your goals, your lifestyle, and your starting point.</p>
			<p>Whether you're recovering from injury, managing a long-term condition, or aiming to perform at a higher level, we meet you where you are and guide you forward.</p>

			<h2>When to Consider Physiotherapy</h2>
			<p>You don't need to wait for things to get worse. Physiotherapy can help if you're dealing with:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Ongoing back or neck pain, including sciatica</li>
				<li>Sports injuries</li>
				<li>Training setbacks — not meeting your running or cycling goals</li>
				<li>Joint pain or stiffness in the shoulder, knee, or hip</li>
				<li>Difficulty moving after surgery or injury</li>
				<li>Balance, coordination, or neurological issues</li>
				<li>Headaches linked to tension or posture</li>
				<li>Pelvic health or developmental concerns</li>
				<li>Dizziness — vestibular issues</li>
			</ul>
			<p>If something doesn't feel right, it's worth seeking our advice.</p>

			<h2>How We Work</h2>
			<p>Everything we do is built around one principle: <strong>helping you move better.</strong></p>
			<p>Your treatment may include:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Hands-on therapy to restore movement</li>
				<li>Targeted exercise to rebuild strength and control</li>
				<li>Progressive loading to prepare you for real-world demands</li>
				<li>Clear education so you understand your condition and recovery</li>
			</ul>
			<p>We don't rely on passive treatment alone. You'll leave each session knowing what you're working towards, and how to get there.</p>

			<h2>Who We Help</h2>
			<p>We work with people across a wide range of needs and experience levels.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Individuals dealing with everyday pain or stiffness</li>
				<li>People like you and top athletes managing injury or performance</li>
				<li>Post-surgical patients rebuilding strength and function</li>
				<li>Children and young people with developmental or sports-related concerns</li>
				<li>Adults managing complex or long-term conditions</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Whatever your starting point, the goal is the same: better movement, better function, better outcomes.</p>

			<h2>Pricing and Insurance</h2>
			<p>We offer a transparent fee structure that reflects our level of clinical expertise. We're also recognised by all major insurance providers, including Bupa and AXA PPP Health.</p>
			<p><a href="/pricing">Pricing Information &rsaquo;</a></p>

			<h2>How We Measure Your Progress</h2>
			<p>We don't guess. From your first session, we establish a clear baseline of how you move, function, and feel. As you progress, we regularly reassess, looking at strength, mobility, pain, and what you can actually do day-to-day. This keeps your treatment focused and accountable.</p>
			<p>For you, that means:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Clear evidence that you're improving</li>
				<li>A plan that adapts as you progress</li>
				<li>Confidence in your return to sport, work, or daily life</li>
			</ul>
			<p><a href="/outcomes">Read more about outcome measures &rsaquo;</a></p>

			<h2>Our Clinical Team</h2>
			<p>Our physiotherapy team is made up of highly experienced clinicians with specialist areas of expertise. You'll be matched with the right practitioner for your needs, whether that's a complex spinal condition, a sports injury, or a long-term neurological issue.</p>
			<p>We work collaboratively, drawing on the depth of experience across the team to ensure your care is both precise and considered.</p>
			<p><a href="/meet-the-team">Meet the team &rsaquo;</a></p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="faq-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="section-header">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-list">
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>Do I need a GP referral?</summary>
					<div class="answer">No. You can book directly with us.</div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>What should I wear?</summary>
					<div class="answer">Comfortable clothing that allows us to assess the area being treated.</div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>How many sessions will I need?</summary>
					<div class="answer">This depends on your condition. After your first session, we'll give you a clear plan.</div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>Can I use my private health insurance?</summary>
					<div class="answer">We recommend everyone checks with their own medical insurance provider with regards to their cover.</div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>What's the difference between a physiotherapist and a consultant physiotherapist?</summary>
					<div class="answer">Consultant physiotherapists have advanced training and extensive experience managing complex cases in their specialist area.</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
